modules.description: Extracts a string prefix from a structured representation, performs wildcard matching against a string, and constructs the structured representation from a string. It operates on an opaque type `t` that encapsulates parsed components. Used to validate and transform user input in a configuration parser.

Handles route matching and parameter extraction from URL paths using pattern-based parsing. Operates on strings and associative lists to map route templates to dynamic segments. Enables efficient routing in web applications by parsing incoming requests against predefined route definitions.

Handles string-to-structure conversion and pattern matching for route definitions, using an opaque type `t` to represent parsed components. Supports wildcard matching, prefix extraction, and reconstruction of structured routes from strings. Enables precise validation and transformation of input in configuration and routing logic. Can be used to parse URL paths, match dynamic segments, and generate route patterns programmatically.
